Tracy Turnblad kind of gal

00:12:42.445 --> 00:12:44.874
with her baby, going to daycare.

00:12:44.874 --> 00:12:46.665
And she said, I can't
take you any further,

00:12:46.665 --> 00:12:48.030
because I have to go to work.

00:12:48.030 --> 00:12:49.080
But she was lovely.

00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:50.412
And it was pouring rain.

00:12:50.412 --> 00:12:51.120
That's the thing.

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:52.800
I did a lot of
research to find out

00:12:52.800 --> 00:12:55.680
the most moderate
temperature on Route 70,

00:12:55.680 --> 00:12:58.350
which was this week in May,
but the thing I didn't look up

00:12:58.350 --> 00:13:00.460
is, it rains every day.

00:13:00.460 --> 00:13:03.480
So the first two days,
I stood there literally

00:13:03.480 --> 00:13:05.280
in pouring down rain.

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:07.190
I thought, I'm
gonna kill myself.

00:13:07.190 --> 00:13:08.047
What book is this?

00:13:08.047 --> 00:13:10.130
MALE SPEAKER 1: So you
never got sick or anything?

00:13:10.130 --> 00:13:10.920
JOHN WATERS: No.

00:13:10.920 --> 00:13:11.215
MALE SPEAKER 1: Wow.

00:13:11.215 --> 00:13:12.989
JOHN WATERS: Well,
I mean-- mentally.

00:13:12.989 --> 00:13:14.456
MALE SPEAKER 2: That
happened a long time ago.

00:13:14.456 --> 00:13:15.539
JOHN WATERS: Oh, car sick.

00:13:15.539 --> 00:13:17.722
My friend told me
the other day--

00:13:17.722 --> 00:13:19.346
MALE SPEAKER 2: Just
lower it a little.

00:13:19.346 --> 00:13:20.012
JOHN WATERS: OK.

00:13:20.012 --> 00:13:23.260
He said, you know, when I was
a child, I always got carsick.

00:13:23.260 --> 00:13:24.830
And you take the
jacket off, look,

00:13:24.830 --> 00:13:26.908
