of the exact medicine

00:13:26.908 --> 00:13:28.740
I had to take as a child.

00:13:28.740 --> 00:13:31.110
I think that was accidental.

00:13:31.110 --> 00:13:34.806
MALE SPEAKER 2: Did
you learn about--

00:13:34.806 --> 00:13:39.204
what did you learn to be the
best techniques to hitchhike?

00:13:39.204 --> 00:13:41.120
JOHN WATERS: With the
sign, humor didn't work.

00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:42.640
I had one that said,
I'm not psycho.

00:13:42.640 --> 00:13:46.390
People laughed but
they didn't pick me up.

00:13:46.390 --> 00:13:47.890
"Writing a book"
really didn't work,

00:13:47.890 --> 00:13:50.900
because then they'd
think, about what?

00:13:50.900 --> 00:13:52.690
And they want their
own private life.

00:13:52.690 --> 00:13:55.372
Something that didn't
work if I was starting out

00:13:55.372 --> 00:13:57.090
in Baltimore instead
of San Francisco.

00:13:57.090 --> 00:13:57.880
It's like a joke.

00:13:57.880 --> 00:14:01.837
You had to have a possible
end, so "End of Route 70," even

00:14:01.837 --> 00:14:04.610
though it was 2000 miles
or something, at least

00:14:04.610 --> 00:14:08.480
meant, please, take me a long
way, but it was possible.

00:14:08.480 --> 00:14:09.400
So it had to be.

00:14:09.400 --> 00:14:12.492
And at the end of
every day, I always

00:14:12.492 --> 00:14:13.950
never wanted to
hitchhike at night.

00:14:13.950 --> 00:14:16.064
So the trick was where
you get dropped off.

00:14:16.064 --> 00:14:17.564
So at the end of
every day, I wanted

00:14:17.564 --> 00:14:19.400
a place that had a hotel.

00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:21.300
So I made this sign
that said, "Next motel."

00:14:21.300 --> 00:14:25.960
I felt like a hooker, so I
just changed it to "hotel"

00:14:25.960 --> 00:14:28.080
even though there
weren't any hotels.

00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:32.390
But it seemed much less tawdry.

00:14:32.390 --> 00:14:37.710
